author: PlayStation
description:
Find the beauty in terror in this new Japanese psychological horror.
 
When Shimizu Hinako's secluded town of Ebisugaoka is consumed by a sudden fog, her once-familiar home becomes a haunting nightmare.

As the town falls silent and the fog thickens, Hinako must navigate the twisted paths of Ebisugaoka, solving complex puzzles and confronting grotesque monsters to survive.

Immerse yourself into Hinako's world as imagined by renowned author Ryukishi07, with entrancing soundscapes by Akira Yamaoka and beautiful visuals in a gripping tale of doubt, regret, and inescapable choices. Will Hinako embrace the beauty hidden within terror, or succumb to the madness that lies ahead?
 
Discover a new chapter in the SILENT HILL series, blending psychological horror with a haunting Japanese setting.

description:
Take play further with the PlayStation Portal™ remote player. 

Facing fierce competition over the TV? It’s quick and easy to switch to the remote player to pick up from where you left off on the big screen - so you can keep playing and keep the peace.  

Want to enjoy your favourite games with some fresh air in the garden or cozy up with them in bed? With immersive DualSense® features* and a 60fps capable** display in your hands, you have the power to transform when and where you play***.  

From squeezing in more time to fully explore open world adventures to discovering new indie gems, find out how the remote player can expand your gaming horizons at playstation.com/editorial/how-playstation-portal-can-expand-your-gaming-horizons/  

Available in original white and now Midnight Black, find your remote player at direct.playstation.com and other participating retailers. 

*Features available when supported by game. 

**Individual game performance will vary based on the specific game

author: PlayStation
description:
https://store.playstation.com/concept/10007196

Dungeons of Hinterberg is Out Now on PlayStation! 
 
A breakout indie hit of 2024, Dungeons of Hinterberg sees you play as Luisa, a lawyer burnt out with the hustle and bustle of city life looking for a relaxing adventure in the Alps. She finds that adventure in Hinterberg – a small alpine town that has mysteriously become host to a madcap collection of dungeons, inhabited by fearsome monsters in need of slaying. And who better to slay them than tourists, looking for a break from the mundane in a snowy wonderland! Explore different biomes, solve puzzles, slay huge bosses - then have a Schnitzel with the locals and other slayers from around the globe to unlock the game’s relationship system. Building deep relationships can unlock special abilities and gameplay systems or give players key items, helping them find their way through a daunting dungeon. With a bit of luck, you and your newfound friends will help uncover the mysteries of Hint

author: PlayStation
description:
Add Baptiste to your wishlist now on PlayStation: https://store.playstation.com/concept/10013181

Step into the unsettling world of Baptiste, a psychological horror game that will push the limits of your sanity.

After a family tragedy, Sara and her son Tom move to Jagged Shore Cliff, a remote coastal area in the United Kingdom, hoping for a fresh start. But their new home holds a dark secret — a sinister doll named Baptiste, locked away in a dusty cabinet with a chilling warning: "Never release this from its glass prison."

What begins as a chance to heal quickly spirals into a harrowing nightmare. Reality twists and fractures as Tom finds himself caught between his inner demons and the sinister force lurking within their home.

The darkness creeps closer with every step. The fear becomes palpable. And the line between what's real and what's imagined begins to blur.

Are you ready to face the terror that awaits?

#ps5 #ps5games #Baptiste #HorrorGame #PlayStation
